{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c84d7771-3855-4c41-b0c8-d251b876512a","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — update the SDK version:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter making the changes, run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nAlso check for any NuGet packages (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) that need version bumps to their .NET 11-compatible releases.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"44e9b837-22a9-4ae2-aad9-38d0cbc14902","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they've described the files. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":285,"requestId":"6826:214D14:5EDB80C:67BFE58:69F010AD"},"id":"43872a05-4195-4785-855d-ec93b2801394","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:43:16.127Z","parentId":"d7b5309a-5906-4018-9757-ce9feb282ff3"}
